Holmes \Holmes\ n. Sherlock Holmes, a fictitious detective in novels by A. Conan Doyle.
Syn: Sherlock Holmes. [WordNet 1.5]

Holmes n 1: a fictitious detective in stories by A. Conan Doyle [syn: {Sherlock Holmes}] 2: United States jurist noted for his liberal opinions (1841-1935) [syn: {Oliver Wendell Holmes Jr.}] 3: United States writer of humorous essays (1809-1894) [syn: {Oliver Wendell Holmes}] 4: English geologist and supporter of the theory of continental drift (1890-1965) [syn: {Arthur Holmes}]
